<item>
            <title>[LU-19417] TCU: misc code cleanup</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19417</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160;Missing &quot;SPDX-License-Identifier: LGPL-2.1+&quot; in liblustre_trash.c&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix typo of &quot;opterative&quot; in lustre/mdd/mdd_device.c&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Handle the overflow of filename appending with timestamp for repeated name deletion:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/ex/lustre-release/+/60666/2..9/lustre/mdd/mdd_trash.c#b597&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/ex/lustre-release/+/60666/2..9/lustre/mdd/mdd_trash.c#b597&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Truncate the name to the available space and hope for the best. It may be that the Y-M-D is enough to de-conflict the name in Trash and is still more useful than not saving the file at all.&lt;br/&gt;
Alternately, drop &quot;Y&quot;, then &quot;M&quot;, then &quot;D&quot; and only use &quot;HH:MM:SS&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;.nsec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; and the timestamps on the inodes should be enough to figure it out?&lt;br/&gt;
Simple solution: truncate to max namelen and hope for no conflicts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and other minor code style needing to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
